# HARD guard (AC#3): the build context must never carry secrets, VCS metadata,
# host tooling, or local state into image layers. Default-deny would be ideal but
# Docker has no "ignore all"; this enumerates every sensitive/irrelevant path.

# --- secrets & credentials (never in a layer) ---
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.crt
**/*token*
**/*secret*
**/.netrc
**/.git-credentials
**/.aws
**/.ssh

# --- VCS / CI metadata ---
**/.git
**/.gitignore
**/.github

# --- local dev / build state ---
**/.venv
**/venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/*.egg-info
**/build
**/dist
**/uv.lock

# --- test/smoke/sidecar scaffolding not needed in the agent runtime image ---
# (egress-proxy has its OWN Dockerfile; seccomp/apparmor are host-side launch
# artifacts the spawner passes via --security-opt, never baked into this image.)
tests
smoke
egress-proxy
seccomp
apparmor

# --- editor / OS cruft ---
**/.DS_Store
**/.idea
**/.vscode
